"title":{
"__html":"Thrombocytopenia"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"78f621",
"children":[
"Thrombocytopenia"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_hm_s21_0",
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"c9351b",
"children":[
"Thrombocytopenia is caused by decreased platelet production, accelerated destruction from consumptive disorders (such as ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"thrombotic thrombocytopenic purpura",
"children":[
"TTP"
]
},
") or autoimmune-mediated destruction, or sequestration of platelets in conditions causing splenomegaly. Disorders associated with decreased bone marrow production often affect other cell lines, causing additional cytopenias. Common causes of nonimmune thrombocytopenia include:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"6e3f1f",
"children":[
"toxins (alcohol)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"0ba0cb",
"children":[
"idiosyncratic drug reactions"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"9d02da",
"children":[
"metastatic cancer"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"1b437c",
"children":[
"infections"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"fb4ecd",
"children":[
"vitamin B",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"12"
]
},
" or folate deficiency"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"7ab95f",
"children":[
"acute leukemia"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"33e9a3",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"myelodysplastic syndromes",
"children":[
"MDS"
]
},
" "
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"8132d2",
"children":[
"Pseudothrombocytopenia occurs if patients have antibodies to ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"ethylenediaminetetraacetic acid",
"children":[
"EDTA"
]
},
","
]
},
" causing platelets to clump together in vitro; an accurate count can be obtained from blood drawn in citrate or heparin."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"88b3f7",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Consumptive thrombocytopenia:"
]
},
" Thrombocytopenia and the presence of schistocytes on the peripheral blood smear suggest disorders such as ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"disseminated intravascular coagulation",
"children":[
"DIC"
]
},
","
]
},
" TTP, and ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"hemolytic uremic syndrome",
"children":[
"HUS"
]
},
"."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"28bc24",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Immune thrombocytopenia"
]
},
" occurs when antibodies targeting platelet antigens mediate accelerated destruction. Diagnosis requires a platelet count <100,000/μL. ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"The characteristic finding is isolated thrombocytopenia in a patient without other apparent causes for the reduced platelets."
]
},
" Antibodies arise in three distinct clinical settings: drug induced, disease associated, and idiopathic. Drug-induced ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"immune thrombocytopenic purpura",
"children":[
"ITP"
]
},
":"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"54e19a",
"children":[
"most often linked to heparin and certain antibiotics"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"dcccc9",
"children":[
"discontinuation of the offending drug should result in platelet recovery"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"004014",
"children":[
"Disease-associated immune thrombocytopenia:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"e7c365",
"children":[
"common causes include HIV and hepatitis C infection (testing always indicated)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"9a23f5",
"children":[
"other causes include hyperthyroidism, hypothyroidism, ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"systemic lupus erythematosus",
"children":[
"SLE"
]
},
" (testing based on compatible findings)"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"2542c3",
"children":[
"ITP:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"be83e5",
"children":[
"peripheral blood smear shows reduced numbers of platelets; some platelets may be large"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"2ed516",
"children":[
"normal erythroid and myeloid cells"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"4176cd",
"children":[
"bone marrow biopsy/aspiration indicated only in older patients with new-onset ITP or if the peripheral blood smear is abnormal"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"17444e",
"children":[
"Anemia does not exclude a diagnosis of ITP if the anemia can be explained by bleeding."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"3efabd",
"children":[
"Measurement of platelet-associated antibody is not helpful because the test lacks both sensitivity and specificity."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
