{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_hm_s21_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f71564",
"children":[
"Initiate therapy for ITP when the platelet count is <30,000/μL or with evidence of bleeding."
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"1974ae",
"children":[
"Glucocorticoids are first-line therapy."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"75ae9d",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"intravenous immune globulin",
"children":[
"IVIG"
]
},
" is indicated for severe thrombocytopenia and life-threatening bleeding."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"fdb156",
"children":[
"Splenectomy or rituximab is indicated for patients who are unresponsive to drug therapy or who relapse after glucocorticoids are tapered."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"c03aeb",
"children":[
"Thrombopoiesis-stimulating agents (romiplostim, eltrombopag) may be attempted in refractory illness."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"2",
